    <text>
        <group>
            <text type="letter" xml:lang="fr">
                <body>
                    
                    <p>Si Vos Altesses Impériales n'ont aucune partie de plaisir arrangée pour ce
                        soir entre six et sept heures, Elles sont invitées à venir en déshabillé
                        sans aucune cérémonie rire ou baîller, comme il leur plaira, a <placeName
                            ref="places.xml#her01">l'Hermitage</placeName>, où l'on donnera gratis
                        les trois misères suivantes:</p>
                    <p><title ref="works.xml#voyage02">Les voyages de M-r Bontemps</title></p>
                    <p><title ref="works.xml#rageau01">La rage au proverbes</title></p>
                    <p><title ref="works.xml#amantb01">L'amant bourru.</title></p>
                    <note type="editorial">On 14 December 1789, Catherine's secretary <ref
                            target="people.xml#khr01">Khrapovitsky</ref> noted: 'Велели играть без
                        собрания на ермитажном театре: "Les voyages de M. Bontemps" et "La rage aux
                        proverbes", для Их Имп[ераторских] Высочеств. Они были приглашены и все сие
                        было исполнено. В дополнение спектакля, дали еще "L'amant bourru"'
                        ('[Catherine] ordered that without an assembly in the Hermitage theatre "The
                        Voygaes of Mr. Goodtimes" and "The Rage for Proverbs" for Their Imperial
                        Highnesses [Paul and Mariya Fedorovna]. They were invited, and all this was
                        carried out. As a supplement to the performance they also played "The Grumpy
                        Lover"'). The present letter is the invitation that <ref
                            target="people.xml#khr01">Khrapovitsky</ref> mentions.</note>
                    <closer><dateline><date when-custom="1789-12-14">Vendredi, 14
                                décembre 1789.</date></dateline></closer>
                </body>
            </text>
            <text type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <body>
                   
                    <p>If Your Imperial Highnesses have no pleasure outing planned for this evening
                        between six and seven o'clock, You are invited to come in informal dress
                        with no ceremony whatsoever, to laugh or to yawn, as you please, to the
                        Hermitage, where the following three nothings will be played for free:</p>
                    <p>The Voyages of Mr. Goodtimes</p>
                    <p>The Rage for Proverbs</p>
                    <p>The Grumpy Lover.</p>
                    <closer><dateline><date when-custom="1789-12-14">Friday, 14
                                December 1789.</date></dateline></closer>
                </body>
            </text>
